<font color="#FF0000">WHAT IF CLINTON IS RIGHT?</font><br>
<tt>Mon Feb  9  1:24:32 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Jed,<br><br>
I have just one thought, and that is that President Clinton was a Vietnam War protestor.  Now, he feels that a strike is necessary against Iraq.  If indeed what he says is heart-felt (and not a ploy, as some think, to relieve him of domestic troubles), then what would convince you that this is needed.  <br><br>
Remember that Cookie, Ed and I have all questioned the way that this might occur.  But saying he is leveling with us about the need to prevent Sadam from having weapons of mass destruction, what would be your feelings?  I am curious.  <br><br>
The reason for my curiosity is, if he does shoot off something at Isrial, and we could have prevented it, what would be our national feelings then?
